First time setup (on FNAL servers):
. init.sh

Environment setup (after first time):
. setup.sh

Instructions for Drift Time Plots / Data:

Run the python script `make_driftV_df.py` on the input ROOT files
(Calibration N-Tuples) you want to process. Then, run the
`DriftTimeMultiRun.ipynb` jupyter notebook on the dataframe files you
want to process. This is done in the jupyter notebook by setting the
location of the `datadir` directory.

